oto\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/buddhafoundation\" class=\"reviewer-name\">buddhafoundation</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">January 7, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Thank you so much for supporting our non-profit organisation with a free pro verison :-)\nNice plugin, does what we need at buddhafoundation.org</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">ByJVea</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/byvea\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4f452060ea19bdf0b93566acd8b7ad07?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4f452060ea19bdf0b93566acd8b7ad07?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/byvea\" class=\"reviewer-name\">byvea</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">January 3, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Conector con muchas utilidades en su versión gratuita, en la PRO es autentcamente profesional. Gracias al equipo de The Events Calendar</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Terrible performance hog</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/negrusti\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a35bc79f9396cf22db1aab7258e06657?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a35bc79f9396cf22db1aab7258e06657?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/negrusti\" class=\"reviewer-name\">negrusti</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">December 29, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Profile/time your PHP execution on fresh WP with and without this plugin installed - you will see what I mean. It gets a lot worse on the sites with actual content.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Good Out-of-Box, but Customizing is a Nightmare</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"2 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"2\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/tzzel\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e5c21e5df4f8e8166d761b61a8ee14f2?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e5c21e5df4f8e8166d761b61a8ee14f2?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/tzzel\" class=\"reviewer-name\">R J <small>(tzzel)</small></a> am <span class=\"review-date\">December 29, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">TLDR: It\'s good out of the box, but for advanced needs, it\'s just difficult to use for customizing, even as a developer. Not planning to use again. \n\nI have tried both the free and pro version. It is a nightmare to customize. Documentation is awful or disorganized -- it\'s basically just a bunch of answered questions they bookmark to serve as \"official documentation.\" I am a WP developer, yet my time customizing how the views are is so difficult. When I try to look at the custom developer functions, it\'s not even on 1 page -- it\'s paginated so I have to keep clicking the next page... why not just put it all on one page so I can see them all and search???? Their archive view is quite awful and has this awkward date picker that chooses one date you want items to be from. FOr my last project, I actually made an event module myself and it outputs events by months, years... Good thing is is does account for location, event organizer, registration URL. Not well thought out beyond that.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Slow Response but Friendly</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"3 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"3\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/marypdickson\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fdb2f7359f470c1dae66c5933b9db283?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/fdb2f7359f470c1dae66c5933b9db283?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/marypdickson\" class=\"reviewer-name\">marypdickson</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">January 9, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I have now had 3 dealings with what shouldn\'t even be called Customer Service.  They are slow to respond and have yet to help me fix my problems after their plugin first crashed our website and then made the calendar disappear. \n\nEdit: The customer service response taking several days for each reply, makes repair processes really slow.  By the time we finally get around to getting to the problem with the plugin, it\'s several weeks of our website calendar being down.  By that point, I was able to wipe all our events and start over and that fixed it.  I really wish they had a phone number so that the problem would\'ve only been for an hour rather than weeks.  Will continue to use them because of their friendliness.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">unuseful</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kmilkus\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/78554c22ed7699c771a23a44bad94663?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/78554c22ed7699c771a23a44bad94663?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/kmilkus\" class=\"reviewer-name\">kmilkus</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">December 25, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I tried to use this plugin for a half of a year, I read a documentation, wrote to support in case I didn\'t understand something. But the thing is, that you should be a developer to use this tool and it \'s easier to create your own calendar, that trying to understand, how every feature is realized. So the calendar:\n1. Is hard to translate,\n2. Has an awful design,\n3. Charges separately for an every feature you need. The calendar price is 80 dollars and if you need tickets or something else, you have to pay once more. Every year! For that price I believe you should have a good working calendar, that you may just install and forget about, and an excellent support (comparing with other offers). That is not the case. You have to spend unbelievable amount of time, to tune the calendar. Now I am using another solution about a year and am more than happy. Don\'t waste your time, like I did. </div>\n</div>\n\";}s:13:\"download_link\";s:68:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/the-events-calendar.4.7.3.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:12:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\