class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"2 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"2\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/thobbes\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3d823ab9d93dc42a9f99e8090565e3ac?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3d823ab9d93dc42a9f99e8090565e3ac?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/thobbes\" class=\"reviewer-name\">thobbes</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">December 4, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">After each update of the plugin something in our Homepage does not work properly anymore. Summarized: If you are always happy about bugs from developers, the program is recommended ;)</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Event Tickets Plus doesn&#039;t work and is a subscription</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/keepsakecidery\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/27e4568df029450d38fa1a6804d71214?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/27e4568df029450d38fa1a6804d71214?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/keepsakecidery\" class=\"reviewer-name\">keepsakecidery</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">November 14, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I feel a bit robbed by the paid version.  Not only didn\'t it work well when integrated into the website, the literature on the internet was limited.  It is a fairly expensive plugin whose updates end in a year.  Again, I was misled into thinking it would still function without updating, but no, the plugin quits completely and bye bye $80.  Not a lot of value considering.  Might as well use Eventbrite.  Easier and only more expensive if you\'re selling gobs of tickets.  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Messy and awkward--paid version probably not worth it</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"2 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"2\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/grantolson\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0cd65a0ee5bf61119462ae548efee54a?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0cd65a0ee5bf61119462ae548efee54a?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/grantolson\" class=\"reviewer-name\">grantolson</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">November 11, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I really wanted to like this plugin, but working with this plugin as a front-end developer has been a real challenge. Some really strange choices in the code, and several inconsistencies.\n\nTo be fair, the free version is probably great for getting a simple calendar of events up and allowing folks to RSVP. It is straightforward to use, and it looks pretty good. Once you get beyond just the basics, however, it feels a little clumsy.\n\nThough it technically works with the WooCommerce, the integration feels sloppy. Creating a ticket creates an item in WooCommerce, but it won\'t display the event image or the event name (just the ticket name) in the cart.\n\nI\'m disappointed, but looking for another solution hasn\'t been easy either. I\'m holding out hope that the developers will invest more time in this add-on to smooth out the bumps, and trying to decide in the meantime if I\'ll ask for a refund in the next few weeks.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great Events Plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/hkayali\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/81c616110ee72d34050271d6ff958858?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/81c616110ee72d34050271d6ff958858?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/hkayali\" class=\"reviewer-name\">hkayali</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">November 7, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I tried a couple of Event Plugins until I landed on The Events Calendar. Very happy in comparison. Nothing is perfect and WordPress is a work in progress constantly being developed and improved. I am happy with the functionality, ease of use, and look of The Events Calendar. I went through the 1 Star reviews and most of them are from ignorant individuals complaining about irrelevant issues. Like \"the plugin doesn\'t send emails\". It\'s not the plugin\'s fault that your emails go to Spam. It\'s an SMTP server issue. Or \"Doesn\'t work\". I mean it really can\'t be true when there are +700,000 active installations of the main plugin and +30,000 of the paid Event Tickets plugin.\n\nCheers...</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Would be nice to try before buying</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"2 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"2\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/wtsadmin\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7e84d22ffbd3a1f9b4a07dc5332feda7?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7e84d22ffbd3a1f9b4a07dc5332feda7?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/wtsadmin\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Dr. D <small>(wtsadmin)</small></a> am <span class=\"review-date\">October 12, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">After installing the plugin a few times and reading all the material I find it is not possible to use the basic version to create an event. The commercial version looks appealing, but unfortunately if I can\'t do anything with the free version I am not compelled to shell out for the one that supposedly works.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Excellent</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/manuelroman\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5ab42da736950fdc8fb84837df443e86?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/5ab42da736950fdc8fb84837df443e86?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/manuelroman\" class=\"reviewer-name\">manuelroman</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">September 20, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">The pro version is perfect to sell ticket.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/louisetimothy\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0d7066034f8b5c121f330908974b9dfd?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0d7066034f8b5c121f330908974b9dfd?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/louisetimothy\" class=\"reviewer-name\">louisetimothy</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">September 6, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Thanks for making this - have been able to figure out and use it without much head scratching and it really helps the engagement on my site.\nI use the ticketing extension and don\'t feel like it adds a huge amount for the cost, but I love the core plugin so much I\'m happy to pay for that.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Nice plugin</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/wxia0822hotmailcom\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/76e254d00e982f69372c3bd324b2bedc?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/76e254d00e982f69372c3bd324b2bedc?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/wxia0822hotmailcom\" class=\"reviewer-name\">wxia0822 <small>(wxia0822@hotmail.com)</small></a> am <span class=\"review-date\">July 14, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">I installed 2 free plugins - this one and \"The event calendar\". Tested everything works fine - the user can purchase a ticket successfully. \n\nNot too many free event plugins allow you to set up event ticket purchasing online. So, they are generous.\n\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Cant Count the Number of Bookings</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pnaybour\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6a728785605e02c45f07c00f382d2184?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6a728785605e02c45f07c00f382d2184?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/pnaybour\" class=\"reviewer-name\">pnaybour</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">May 23, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Ok but it has a big bug, it can\'t account for cancellation in an event. So if you have 20 tickets for an event and 10 are sold but 3 are cancelled it reported the number of atendees as 10 with 10 seats left. It ignores the cancellations. This is a basic function for a events management software and needs to be fixed. </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">HORRIBLE DO NOT BUY</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 von 5 Sternen\" data-title-template=\"%s von 5 Sternen\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Von <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rebecca1964\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/697d76646d63108a9c5c521b4b6c997c?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/697d76646d63108a9c5c521b4b6c997c?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rebecca1964\" class=\"reviewer-name\">rebecca1964</a> am <span class=\"review-date\">April 24, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">About 10-20 percent of our ticket holders have not been able to download their tickets... they get blocked by their email providers as spam, and then lost in cyberspace somewhere. I have spent HOURS sending tickets individually... be warned.... do not buy this product! I\'m am switching to Eventbrite within one month of a major event and I am not happy. </div>\n</div>\n\";}s:13:\"download_link\";s:62:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/event-tickets.4.9.4.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:9:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=1839593\";s:7:\"caption\";s:24:\"RSVP and ticket on event\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=1839593\";s:7:\"caption\";s:24:\"Front-end ticket in page\";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1839593\";s:7:\"caption\";s:15:\"PayPal checkout\";}i:4;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=1841640\";s:7:\"caption\";s:15:\"Attendee report\";}i:5;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=1762315\";s:7:\"caption\";s:14:\"Emailed ticket\";}i:6;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=1839593\";s:7:\"caption\";s:19:\"Ticket confirmation\";}i:7;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=1841640\";s:7:\"caption\";s:14:\"Event settings\";}i:8;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:66:\"https://ps.w.org/event-tickets/asset